--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Discharge module for `decode-rel-resp-вү…бҙҙ-atomic-compound-0E` from
-- `RespIso/AtomicCompound.agda`.
--
-- ## Goal
--
-- Given an atomic `f : HomTerm A B` (one of `id, О»вҮ’, О»вҮҗ, ПҒвҮ’, ПҒвҮҗ, ОұвҮ’,
-- ОұвҮҗ, Пғ` вҖ” the Agen case is handled separately by edge-count
-- arithmetic) and a compound `g : HomTerm A B` (i.e. `_вҲҳ_` or `_вҠ—вӮҒ_`)
-- whose translation has zero edges, plus an iso `вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«`,
-- show `decode-rel f вүҲTerm decode-rel g`.
--
-- ## Why `g` is "structural"
--
-- Edge counts are additive across `_вҲҳ_` and `_вҠ—вӮҒ_`:
--
--   * `nE вҹӘ h вҲҳ k вҹ«  = nE вҹӘ h вҹ« + nE вҹӘ k вҹ«`
--   * `nE вҹӘ h вҠ—вӮҒ k вҹ« = nE вҹӘ h вҹ« + nE вҹӘ k вҹ«`
--
-- and `nE вҹӘ Agen _ вҹ« вүЎ 1`.  So `nE вҹӘ g вҹ« вүЎ 0` propagates inductively:
-- every sub-term of `g` has zero edges, which rules out every `Agen`
-- node anywhere inside `g`.  We encode this as the `Structural`
-- predicate below вҖ” a syntactic witness "no `Agen` subterm" вҖ” and
-- prove the equivalence `nE вҹӘ g вҹ« вүЎ 0  вҶ”  Structural g`.
--
-- Both `f` (a structural atomic constructor) and `g` (a structural
-- compound) therefore live in the fragment generated by
-- `id, О»вҮ’, О»вҮҗ, ПҒвҮ’, ПҒвҮҗ, ОұвҮ’, ОұвҮҗ, Пғ` under `_вҲҳ_, _вҠ—вӮҒ_`.  At the level
-- of `FreeMonoidal` this is exactly the *coherence fragment*: the
-- symmetric monoidal coherence theorem (Mac Lane + braiding) says any
-- two morphisms of the same type in this fragment whose underlying
-- permutations agree are `вүҲTerm`-equal.  The iso `вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«`
-- forces the underlying permutations to agree (both hypergraphs have
-- 0 edges, so they are entirely characterised by their boundary
-- permutations, and the iso provides a ПҶ matching dom/cod up to
-- relabelling).
--
-- Constructive discharge requires the symmetric-monoidal coherence
-- solver (the existing `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` covers
-- the Mac Lane fragment but not Пғ; see
-- `Hypergraph.Completeness.CoherenceSolver` for the current limit).
-- Pending that solver extension, we narrow the original postulate to
-- a `Structural`-restricted form whose hypothesis is exactly the
-- "symmetric monoidal coherence on the structural fragment" claim.
--
-- ## What this module exports
--
-- * `Structural`             вҖ” syntactic predicate "no `Agen` subterm".
-- * `nE-0вҶ’Structural`        вҖ” `nE вҹӘ g вҹ« вүЎ 0 вҶ’ Structural g`,
--                              fully constructive.
-- * `Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm`
--                            вҖ” the *narrowed* postulate: any two
--                              structural terms of the same type with
--                              isomorphic translations are `вүҲTerm`-equal
--                              at the `FreeMonoidal` level (i.e. `f вүҲTerm g`
--                              directly, no `decode-rel`/`bridge` wrapping).
--                              This is exactly Mac Lane's symmetric
--                              monoidal coherence theorem on the
--                              `id, О», ПҒ, Оұ, Пғ`-fragment.
-- * `Structural-coherence`   вҖ” derived: `decode-rel f вүҲTerm decode-rel g`,
--                              obtained from `Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm`
--                              by passing through `decode-roundtrip-rel`
--                              and the `bridge`-congruence.
-- * `decode-rel-resp-вү…бҙҙ-atomic-compound-0E` вҖ” the original lemma,
--                              derived from the above ingredients
--                              together with the `Atomic вҮ’ Structural`
--                              fact.
--
-- ## Why this narrowing is strict
--
-- The original postulate had conclusion `decode-rel f вүҲTerm decode-rel g`,
-- whose unfolding involves `bridge`, `unflatten-flatten-вүҲ`, and the
-- structural recursion of `decode-rel` through `вҲҳ` and `вҠ—вӮҒ`.  The
-- narrowed conclusion `f вүҲTerm g` lives purely in the free symmetric
-- monoidal category over the signature, with no decode plumbing вҖ” it
-- is exactly the statement of categorical coherence for the
-- non-generator (a.k.a. `Structural`) fragment.
--
-- The derivation back to the original form uses only existing
-- constructive lemmas:
--   * `decode-roundtrip-rel f : decode-rel f вүҲTerm bridge f`     (proved)
--   * `decode-roundtrip-rel g : decode-rel g вүҲTerm bridge g`     (proved)
--   * `bridge` is a congruence wrt `вүҲTerm`                       (1-line proof)
-- so the original lemma is `decode-roundtrip-rel f ; bridge-cong ; sym (decode-roundtrip-rel g)`.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

