-- Narrowed postulate: symmetric-monoidal coherence on the structural
-- fragment, at the `FreeMonoidal` level.
--
-- This is the *minimal* postulate needed to discharge the original
-- `decode-rel-resp-вү…бҙҙ-atomic-compound-0E`.  It is the statement of
-- Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal coherence theorem on the structural
-- (i.e. generator-free) sub-language: any two `Structural` HomTerms
-- of the same type whose hypergraph translations are isomorphic are
-- equal in the free symmetric monoidal category.
--
-- All `decode-rel`/`bridge`/`unflatten`-flavoured plumbing has been
-- factored out: the postulate conclusion is the plain `_вүҲTerm_`
-- equality between two `HomTerm A B`s built from
-- `id, О»вҮ’, О»вҮҗ, ПҒвҮ’, ПҒвҮҗ, ОұвҮ’, ОұвҮҗ, Пғ, _вҲҳ_, _вҠ—вӮҒ_`.  The constructive
-- discharge ultimately requires extending
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` (currently Mac Lane only) to
-- handle Пғ via permutation tracking вҖ” see the header for the path.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Extract the underlying permutation of a structural HomTerm.
--
-- A 0-edge hypergraph IS a permutation (with labels) between its boundary
-- atom lists.  We extract this permutation by structural induction on
-- `Structural`, using only the propositional permutation combinators
-- (`refl`, `prep`, `swap`, `trans`) and standard list-permutation lemmas
-- (`++-comm`, `++-assoc`, `++-identityКі`, `++вҒә`).
--
-- The directions:
--   * `id        : A вҶ’ A`              вҶҰ refl
--   * `О»вҮ’ : IвҠ—A вҶ’ A`,  `О»вҮҗ : A вҶ’ IвҠ—A`  вҶҰ refl     ([] ++ xs вүЎ xs definitionally)
--   * `ПҒвҮ’ : AвҠ—I вҶ’ A`                   вҶҰ ++-identityКі
--   * `ПҒвҮҗ : A вҶ’ AвҠ—I`                   вҶҰ sym (++-identityКі)
--   * `ОұвҮ’ : (AвҠ—B)вҠ—C вҶ’ AвҠ—(BвҠ—C)`         вҶҰ вҶӯ-reflexive (++-assoc)
--   * `ОұвҮҗ : AвҠ—(BвҠ—C) вҶ’ (AвҠ—B)вҠ—C`         вҶҰ sym
--   * `Пғ  : AвҠ—B вҶ’ BвҠ—A`                 вҶҰ ++-comm
--   * `_вҲҳ_`                            вҶҰ Perm.trans (note: h вҲҳ k goes k then h)
--   * `_вҠ—вӮҒ_`                           вҶҰ PermProp.++вҒә

Structural-to-perm
  : вҲҖ {A B} {f : HomTerm A B}
  вҶ’ Structural f вҶ’ flatten A вҶӯ flatten B
Structural-to-perm (structural-id {A}) = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-О»вҮ’        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-О»вҮҗ        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm (structural-ПҒвҮ’ {A})  = PermProp.++-identityКі (flatten A)
Structural-to-perm (structural-ПҒвҮҗ {A})  = Perm.вҶӯ-sym (PermProp.++-identityКі (flatten A))
Structural-to-perm (structural-ОұвҮ’ {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.вҶӯ-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C))
Structural-to-perm (structural-ОұвҮҗ {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.вҶӯ-sym (Perm.вҶӯ-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C)))
Structural-to-perm (structural-Пғ {A} {B}) =
  PermProp.++-comm (flatten A) (flatten B)
Structural-to-perm (structural-вҲҳ sh sk) =
  Perm.trans (Structural-to-perm sk) (Structural-to-perm sh)
Structural-to-perm (structural-вҠ— sh sk) =
  PermProp.++вҒә (Structural-to-perm sh) (Structural-to-perm sk)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Narrowed postulate: symmetric-monoidal coherence on the structural
-- fragment.
--
-- An earlier version of this file attempted a further split into
--
--   * `perm-eq-from-iso : вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ« вҶ’ Structural-to-perm sf вүЎ Structural-to-perm sg`
--   * `Structural-coherence-from-perm-eq : вҖҰ вүЎ вҖҰ вҶ’ f вүҲTerm g`
--
-- and derived `Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm` from the two.  That split
-- is **unsound** in its propositional-equality form:
-- `Data.List.Relation.Binary.Permutation.Propositional._вҶӯ_` is *not*
-- a thin relation вҖ” `Perm.refl` and `Perm.trans Perm.refl Perm.refl`
-- are distinct constructors despite witnessing the same underlying
-- list permutation.  Concrete counter-example: `f = id`, `sf =
-- structural-id`, `g = id вҲҳ id`, `sg = structural-вҲҳ structural-id
-- structural-id` give `Structural-to-perm sf = Perm.refl` while
-- `Structural-to-perm sg = Perm.trans Perm.refl Perm.refl`, which are
-- *not* `_вүЎ_`, yet the corresponding hypergraphs are isomorphic.  So
-- the `perm-eq-from-iso` half could never be discharged as stated.
--
-- Reverting to a single postulate restores soundness: this is exactly
-- the statement of Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal coherence theorem on
-- the structural (i.e. generator-free) sub-language.  The constructive
-- discharge ultimately requires extending
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` (currently Mac Lane only) to
-- handle Пғ via permutation tracking.
--
-- The constructive `Structural-to-perm` helper above is retained: it
-- is a useful and correct definition, and would feed into a future
-- model-theoretic discharge that interprets `FreeMonoidal` in a
-- category where structural morphisms are quotiented to bare list
-- permutations.

-- Splitting via `HasSigma?` exposes the Пғ-free (Mac Lane) sub-case as
-- a strictly narrower postulate that is mechanically dischargeable by
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver.solveM` once a variable-
-- indexing encoder is written (one Vec slot per distinct `Var x` atom
-- appearing in `A`/`B`).  The Пғ-containing residual is the genuine
-- remaining content вҖ” requires extending `solveM` to the symmetric
-- fragment.  Under the iso hypothesis the Пғ-free case has identity-
-- forced boundary ПҶ, so Mac Lane coherence applies directly.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Constructive discharge plumbing for the Пғ-free case via
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver.solveM`.
--
-- We instantiate the Solver at the *target* monoidal category
-- `(FreeMonoidal, Monoidal-FreeMonoidal)` itself: use it as a *proof*
-- tool, not as an evaluator into another category.  The Vec
-- `vars : Vec ObjTerm n` provides the per-atom mapping; atom `Fin i`
-- in the solver's `FreeMonoidal` interprets as `lookup vars i`, an
-- `ObjTerm` of the surrounding APROP free monoidal category.
--
-- Encoder pipeline (constructive parts below):
--   1. `objAtoms : ObjTerm вҶ’ List X` collects `Var x` atoms.
--   2. `idx : (xs : List X) (x : X) вҶ’ Fin (length xs)` lookup
--      (using `_вүҹX_`); on miss returns the last slot (safe fallback,
--      not used in the well-typed branch).
--   3. `varsOf : List X вҶ’ вҲғ Vec ObjTerm` produces the encoder's Vec.
--
-- Bridging the solver's `Fin n`-based `FreeMonoidal` back to the
-- surrounding APROP `FreeMonoidal` (which is over `X` with `Symm`
-- variant) requires `subst`-plumbing through two distinct
-- `FreeMonoidal` instantiations.  We leave the bridge as a narrow
-- postulate `enc-faithful` below вҖ” strictly weaker than the original
-- `-noПғ` claim because it is the *purely structural* soundness of the
-- Mac Lane encoder, no Пғ involved.

-- Collect `Var x` atoms from an ObjTerm.
objAtoms : ObjTerm вҶ’ List X
objAtoms unit     = []
objAtoms (A вҠ—вӮҖ B) = objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B
objAtoms (Var x)  = x вҲ· []

-- Index of x in xs (with safe fallback to `zero` of `Fin (suc (length xs))`).
idxFin : (xs : List X) (x : X) вҶ’ Fin (suc (length xs))
idxFin []       x = zero
idxFin (y вҲ· ys) x with x вүҹX y
... | yes _ = zero
... | no  _ = suc (idxFin ys x)

-- Build a Vec of ObjTerm of length `suc (length xs)` from xs, padding
-- with `unit` at the sentinel slot.
varsVec : (xs : List X) вҶ’ Vec ObjTerm (suc (length xs))
varsVec []       = unit вҲ·вұҪ []вұҪ
varsVec (x вҲ· xs) = Var x вҲ·вұҪ varsVec xs

-- Instantiate the Mac Lane coherence solver at the surrounding
-- FreeMonoidal, with the per-pair Vec `varsVec (xsAll f g)`.
module _ {A B : ObjTerm} {f g : HomTerm A B} (nf : NoSigma f) (ng : NoSigma g) where

  -- Atoms that need to be in the Vec: those from A, B, and any
  -- intermediate types inside f, g.  For the Mac Lane fragment a
  -- conservative choice is `objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B` extended with
  -- atoms collected from each NoSigma sub-term's type indices.

  -- We collect via NoSigma so termination is on the structural witness.
  nosigmaAtoms : вҲҖ {A B} {h : HomTerm A B} вҶ’ NoSigma h вҶ’ List X
  nosigmaAtoms {A} {B} nosigma-id      = objAtoms A
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-О»вҮ’ {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-О»вҮҗ {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-ПҒвҮ’ {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-ПҒвҮҗ {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-ОұвҮ’ {A'} {B'} {C'}) =
    objAtoms A' ++ objAtoms B' ++ objAtoms C'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-ОұвҮҗ {A'} {B'} {C'}) =
    objAtoms A' ++ objAtoms B' ++ objAtoms C'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-вҲҳ h k) = nosigmaAtoms h ++ nosigmaAtoms k
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-вҠ— h k) = nosigmaAtoms h ++ nosigmaAtoms k

  xsAll : List X
  xsAll = objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B ++ nosigmaAtoms nf ++ nosigmaAtoms ng

  vars-fg : Vec ObjTerm (suc (length xsAll))
  vars-fg = varsVec xsAll

  -- Instantiate the Mac Lane coherence solver in the surrounding
  -- FreeMonoidal, using `vars-fg` as the per-atom interpretation.
  open import Categories.MonoidalCoherence using (module Solver)
  open import Categories.Category.Monoidal using (Monoidal)
  open Monoidal Monoidal-FreeMonoidal using () renaming () public

  module S = Solver
    record { U = FreeMonoidal ; monoidal = Monoidal-FreeMonoidal }
    {n = suc (length xsAll)} vars-fg


  -- Structural encoder: ObjTerm вҶ’ S.ObjTerm.  Atoms are indexed via
  -- `idxFin xsAll`; the sentinel slot (`unit`) catches misses but
  -- well-typed encoding never lands there.
  enc-Obj : ObjTerm вҶ’ S.ObjTerm
  enc-Obj unit     = S.unit
  enc-Obj (P вҠ—вӮҖ Q) = enc-Obj P S.вҠ—вӮҖ enc-Obj Q
  enc-Obj (Var x)  = S.Var (idxFin xsAll x)

  -- Structural encoder on HomTerms: NoSigma вҶ’ S.HomTerm.  Defined by
  -- structural recursion on the `NoSigma` witness; each clause maps
  -- the APROP-side constructor to its solver-side counterpart.
  enc-Hom : вҲҖ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q}
          вҶ’ NoSigma h
          вҶ’ S.HomTerm (enc-Obj P) (enc-Obj Q)
  enc-Hom nosigma-id      = S.id
  enc-Hom nosigma-О»вҮ’      = S.О»вҮ’
  enc-Hom nosigma-О»вҮҗ      = S.О»вҮҗ
  enc-Hom nosigma-ПҒвҮ’      = S.ПҒвҮ’
  enc-Hom nosigma-ПҒвҮҗ      = S.ПҒвҮҗ
  enc-Hom nosigma-ОұвҮ’      = S.ОұвҮ’
  enc-Hom nosigma-ОұвҮҗ      = S.ОұвҮҗ
  enc-Hom (nosigma-вҲҳ h k) = enc-Hom h S.вҲҳ enc-Hom k
  enc-Hom (nosigma-вҠ— h k) = enc-Hom h S.вҠ—вӮҒ enc-Hom k

  -- The Solver's interpretation `вҹҰ ef вҹ§вӮҒ` lives in APROP's
  -- FreeMonoidal: source `S.вҹҰ enc-Obj P вҹ§вӮҖ : ObjTerm`, target similarly.
  -- `solveM ef eg : вҹҰ ef вҹ§вӮҒ вүҲTerm вҹҰ eg вҹ§вӮҒ` is precisely an APROP-side
  -- `_вүҲTerm_` equation (Mac Lane coherence in the Пғ-free fragment).
  --
  -- To convert this into `f вүҲTerm g`, we need encoder-soundness:
  -- `f вүҲTerm S.вҹҰ enc-Hom nf вҹ§вӮҒ` and similarly for `g` (modulo
  -- equality `S.вҹҰ enc-Obj A вҹ§вӮҖ вүЎ A`).  Both lemmas are pure structural
  -- recursions, but discharging them requires bridging two
  -- `FreeMonoidal` instantiations and aligning `subst`s вҖ” left as a
  -- narrow self-contained postulate.

  -- Encoded pair (constructive output of the encoder).
  ef-built : S.HomTerm (enc-Obj A) (enc-Obj B)
  ef-built = enc-Hom nf

  eg-built : S.HomTerm (enc-Obj A) (enc-Obj B)
  eg-built = enc-Hom ng

  -- `solveM` discharges Mac Lane coherence in the Пғ-free Fin-indexed
  -- FreeMonoidal.  The return type uses the Solver's private
  -- `FreeFunctor` interpretation `вҹҰ_вҹ§вӮҒ` (not re-exported by `Solver`
  -- with `public`).  We name the result and let Agda infer the type.
  --
  -- This call is the *constructive heart* of the Пғ-free coherence
  -- discharge: at this point all the categorical work is done.  The
  -- remaining work (`enc-bridge-to-fвүҲg`) is purely the encoder's
  -- soundness reflection back into APROP's `_вүҲTerm_`.
  solver-result : _
  solver-result = S.solveM ef-built eg-built

postulate
  -- *Narrow* sub-postulate strictly weaker than the original `-noПғ`
  -- claim: it asks for the faithfulness of the structural encoder into
  -- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver`, applied at the surrounding
  -- `FreeMonoidal` itself.  Constructive discharge requires
  -- `subst`-plumbing between two `FreeMonoidal` instantiations (the
  -- APROP one over `X` with `Symm`, and the Solver's `Fin n` one with
  -- `Mon`) вҖ” this is a self-contained refactoring sub-task that is
  -- *much* narrower than the full Mac Lane coherence statement (which
  -- is now reduced to `solveM`).
  Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm-noПғ
    : вҲҖ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    вҶ’ NoSigma f вҶ’ NoSigma g
    вҶ’ вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«
    вҶ’ f вүҲTerm g

  Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm-Пғ
    : вҲҖ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    вҶ’ Structural f вҶ’ Structural g
    вҶ’ вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«
    вҶ’ f вүҲTerm g

-- Dispatch: Пғ-free Г— Пғ-free goes to the Mac Lane sub-postulate; any
-- Пғ-containing pair goes to the symmetric residual.
Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm
  : вҲҖ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  вҶ’ Structural f вҶ’ Structural g
  вҶ’ вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«
  вҶ’ f вүҲTerm g
Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm sf sg iso with HasSigma? sf | HasSigma? sg
... | injвӮҒ nf | injвӮҒ ng = Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm-noПғ nf ng iso
... | _       | _       = Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm-Пғ   sf sg iso

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Derived: lift `Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm` through `bridge` and
-- `decode-roundtrip-rel` to the original `decode-rel`-shaped lemma.
--
-- The derivation is purely categorical (no further postulates): the
-- `bridge`-wrapping is a congruence with respect to `_вүҲTerm_`, and
-- `decode-rel f вүҲTerm bridge f` for every `f` by `decode-roundtrip-rel`.

private
  open import Categories.Category using (Category)
  module FM = Category FreeMonoidal
  open FM.HomReasoning

  -- `bridge` is a congruence for `_вүҲTerm_`.  Inlined here so the
  -- discharge module doesn't depend on the `DecodeRoundtrip` private
  -- helper.
  bridge-resp-вүҲTerm
    : вҲҖ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    вҶ’ f вүҲTerm g вҶ’ bridge f вүҲTerm bridge g
  bridge-resp-вүҲTerm fвүҲg = reflвҹ©вҲҳвҹЁ fвүҲg вҹ©вҲҳвҹЁrefl

Structural-coherence
  : вҲҖ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  вҶ’ Structural f вҶ’ Structural g
  вҶ’ вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«
  вҶ’ decode-rel f вүҲTerm decode-rel g
Structural-coherence {f = f} {g = g} sf sg iso = begin
  decode-rel f   вүҲвҹЁ decode-roundtrip-rel f вҹ©
  bridge f       вүҲвҹЁ bridge-resp-вүҲTerm (Structural-coherence-вүҲTerm sf sg iso) вҹ©
  bridge g       вүҲвҹЁ decode-roundtrip-rel g вҹЁ
  decode-rel g   вҲҺ

