-- Discharge the original postulate.
--
-- `Atomic f` + `nE вҹӘ f вҹ« вүЎ 0` вҮ’ `Structural f` (rules out `Agen`).
-- For the atomic shapes routed into the `вҖҰ-0E` case from
-- `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`, the atomic-side edge count is
-- 0 by construction (see `nE-{id,О»вҮ’,О»вҮҗ,ПҒвҮ’,ПҒвҮҗ,ОұвҮ’,ОұвҮҗ,Пғ}` there) вҖ” we
-- recover that here by case-splitting on the `Atomic` witness rather
-- than threading the edge-count proof through the API.

-- The originally-postulated lemma.  Note: the `Atomic f` hypothesis
-- combined with the dispatch from `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`
-- guarantees that `f` is *not* `Agen` (the Agen branch routes to
-- `decode-rel-resp-вү…бҙҙ-Agen-compound-1E` instead).  We extract a
-- `Structural f` witness by case-analysis on `Atomic f`, where the
-- `Agen` branch is dismissed via the iso witness's edge-count
-- transport (a `Fin 1 вҶ” Fin 0` contradiction).

-- The discharge of `decode-rel-resp-вү…бҙҙ-atomic-compound-0E`.  Note we
-- *drop* the redundant `Compound g` hypothesis: under
-- `nE вҹӘ g вҹ« вүЎ 0`, the `Compound g` argument carries no information
-- beyond the boundary types, since `Structural g` is recovered from
-- the edge-count witness alone (see `nE-0вҶ’Structural`).  Dropping it
-- breaks an otherwise-circular import between `AtomicCompound.agda`
-- (which defines `Compound`) and this module.  The caller in
-- `AtomicCompound.agda` ignores the redundant argument when wiring up.

decode-rel-resp-вү…бҙҙ-atomic-compound-0E
  : вҲҖ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  вҶ’ Atomic f
  вҶ’ nE вҹӘ g вҹ« вүЎ 0
  вҶ’ вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«
  вҶ’ decode-rel f вүҲTerm decode-rel g
decode-rel-resp-вү…бҙҙ-atomic-compound-0E {f = f} {g = g} af g-nEвүЎ0 iso =
  Structural-coherence
    (atomicвҶ’structural af)
    (nE-0вҶ’Structural g g-nEвүЎ0)
    iso
  where
    -- The `Agen` branch of `Atomic f` is incompatible with
    -- `вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«` when `nE вҹӘ g вҹ« вүЎ 0`: the iso induces a
    -- bijection `Fin 1 вҶ” Fin 0`, which is absurd.  We discharge it by
    -- routing `ПҲ : Fin (nE вҹӘ Agen _ вҹ«) вҶ’ Fin (nE вҹӘ g вҹ«)` and then
    -- transporting along `nE вҹӘ g вҹ« вүЎ 0`.
    open import Data.Fin using (Fin; zero)
    open import Relation.Binary.PropositionalEquality using (subst; sym)

    Fin-zero-empty : Fin 0 вҶ’ вҠҘ
    Fin-zero-empty ()

    -- In the `Agen` branch of `Atomic f`, the original `iso :
    -- вҹӘ f вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«` becomes `вҹӘ Agen h вҹ« вү…бҙҙ вҹӘ g вҹ«` (with
    -- `nE вҹӘ Agen h вҹ« вүЎ 1`), so `ПҲ zero : Fin (nE вҹӘ g вҹ«) = Fin 0`.
    atomicвҶ’structural : Atomic f вҶ’ Structural f
    atomicвҶ’structural (atomic-Agen h) =
      вҠҘ-elim (Fin-zero-empty (subst Fin g-nEвүЎ0 (_вү…бҙҙ_.ПҲ iso zero)))
    atomicвҶ’structural atomic-id        = structural-id
    atomicвҶ’structural atomic-О»вҮ’        = structural-О»вҮ’
    atomicвҶ’structural atomic-О»вҮҗ        = structural-О»вҮҗ
    atomicвҶ’structural atomic-ПҒвҮ’        = structural-ПҒвҮ’
    atomicвҶ’structural atomic-ПҒвҮҗ        = structural-ПҒвҮҗ
    atomicвҶ’structural atomic-ОұвҮ’        = structural-ОұвҮ’
    atomicвҶ’structural atomic-ОұвҮҗ        = structural-ОұвҮҗ
    atomicвҶ’structural (atomic-Пғ вҰғ s вҰ„) = structural-Пғ вҰғ s вҰ„
